<br>
Last night three guildies went into the entrance of the Hole for an experience group.<br>
<br>
53 Paladin, 52 Warrior and a 51 Druid.<br>
<br>
the paladin got 1/2 of a blue<br>
the druid got 3/4 of a blue<br>
the warrior got 1/16 of a blue <br>
<br>
in the first hour.<br>
<br>
They compared and thought something was buggy, so they camped out, reformed and hunted the next hour with no change in the experience again.<br>
<br>
Any ideas why that would be the result?  <br>
<br>
Yes, they know how to compare the % correctly ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just wanted to get some feedback<br>
<br>
Kassel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/02 6:25:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15350.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: weird experience incident</span><hr size=1> I don't have any magic explanation that would explain all that.  As I understand it some of the variables are:<br>
<br>
- The higher level players would get slightly more of the experience points, but that would be pretty negligable between 51-53 players, and would be offset in the graphical xp bar by teh fact that the higher level players need more xp points to level.  In fact the higher xp requirements might be the bigger factor, which might lead to the lower level players getting more &quot;blue&quot; than the higher level players.<br>
<br>
- Racial xp modifiers are still in the game.  Halflings have a racial xp bonus, they level faster than other races.  Races like Ogres (you didn't mention what race the warrior was) level slower than other races.  It's not as big a gap as the class modifiers used to be before they were removed, but it does have some effect.<br>
<br>
Other than that I'd chalk it up to either someone being mistaken (maybe comparing yellow against blue?), someone having partial alt adv xp turned on, or just a graphical glitch since 1-2 hours isn't a long sample time and comparing 1/16 of a blue to 1/2 a blue, or 1/2 blue to 3/4 blue isn't a huge difference.  I think the blue bar has been known to jump around a bit, it might have evened out over a longer time period. <p><BR>
